mocha.wrappers.jbdd
Class jbddManager

java.lang.Object
  mocha.wrappers.jbdd.jbddManager

public class jbddManager
extends java.lang.Object

java wrapper to a BDD package. This defines a jbddManager and a jbdd class. The following functions are exported in the jbddManager class. See the BDD package for documentation of each of these functions. Since java does not support enumerated types, bdd_reorder_type_t and bdd_reorder_verbosity_t are handled as strings. For instance, if you want the default verbosity, pass the String "BDD_REORDER_VERBOSITY_DEFAULT" as the argument. We have not exported any functions that require a bdd node or return a bdd_node because we strongly believe that the user of a BDD package should never worry about this.
